The paper discusses communication complexity lower bounds using polynomials, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the communication of information between parties. The use of polynomials in the paper also suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the study of patterns and matrices, which is a topic that falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
